Here is a focused, curated list of 160+ mostly medium/hard LeetCode problems that cover all the standard patterns in 12 days.

The list is synthesized from NeetCode 150, Blind 75, LeetCode Top Interview 150, Curated Algo 170

How to use this in 12 days (5–8h/day)
Goal: Get pattern coverage + implementation speed on medium/hard problems.

Strategy:

Focus on patterns, not just questions. For each problem, explicitly label which pattern you’re using (sliding window, two pointers, etc.).

Per day target: 6–8 new problems + 2–3 revisits.

40–60 minutes/problem including dry‑run + writing code + self‑review.

Priority: Within each category below, the first 5–7 problems are “Tier‑1 / must‑do” for that pattern. If you run low on time, focus on those and skim the rest.

Language: Do everything in C++ (or your embedded language of choice) without STL “magic” you couldn’t reproduce in C (especially for heaps, queues, maps).

Day‑by‑day high‑level plan:

Day 1–2: Arrays / Hashing / Strings, Sliding Window & Two Pointers

Day 3: Binary Search, Prefix/Suffix, Sorting‑based tricks

Day 4: Stacks / Monotonic stacks, basic math/bit

Day 5: Linked Lists, LRU style design, a few heaps

Day 6–7: Trees & BST (traversals, construction, DFS/BFS, tree DP)

Day 8: Graphs (BFS/DFS, topo sort, union‑find flavor)

Day 9: Backtracking / recursion, tries

Day 10: DP 1D / 2D (classic interview set)

Day 11: Intervals & Greedy + revisit questions

Day 12: Two full mock sessions: 2 x 45‑min interviews using mixed questions from list, strict timing.

